{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdHDNMpcQE6jNjqXQ9nTU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed and verified. Both tests pass.\n\n## What was wrong\n\n**Root cause:** `orderTotalCents` in `src/money.js` violated its own documented spec. The docstring says the discount applies to the **order subtotal**, rounded to the nearest cent **once**. But the code rounded *each line separately* inside the loop and then summed the rounded values.\n\nPer-line rounding can drift by up to half a cent per line. In the reproduction — two `$8.99` lines at 50% off — each line computes `449.5` cents, which rounds *up* to `450`, summing to `900` (`$9.00`). Rounding the true subtotal once gives `1798 × 0.5 = 899` (`$8.99`) — the correct promo price.\n\n## The fix\n\n```js\nlet subtotal = 0;\nfor (const line of lines) {\n  subtotal += line.unitCents * line.qty;   // exact integer subtotal\n}\nreturn Math.round(subtotal * (1 - discountPct / 100));  // discount + round ONCE\n```\n\nThis makes `invoice.js` and `report.js` (both of which call `orderTotalCents`) agree with the promo pricing, so billing and checkout will no longer disagree by a cent. I added a regression test in `test/money.test.js` capturing the exact `$8.99` case.\n\nOne thing worth flagging for later (I left it alone since it's outside this bug): `report.js:6` has a `// TODO: rounding here is sketchy?` comment, but its `toFixed(2)` on already-integer cents is fine now that the cents value is correct."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":323,"cache_read_input_tokens":30287,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":323},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8983e030-4c8c-4583-a53c-2c004e830b8e","uuid":"1776d86f-832a-4d94-ad21-426eb7daa21d